# Glossary of Syruponium V9.0 Terminology

This document defines the specialized mechanical and fluid-dynamic terms used throughout the Syruponium codebase and theoretical simulations.

| Term | Definition | Context in Code |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **Syruponium** | The universal superfluid medium (Non-Newtonian Superfluid). | The global simulation environment/field. |
| **Syrupon** | The fundamental discrete particle/quanta of the medium. | The individual agent or node in particle-based sims. |
| **Syruponic Gradient** | The pressure differential that replaces classical gravity. | The vector field governing motion/acceleration. |
| **Braking Epoch** | The phase where viscosity ($w \approx 0.72$) limits expansion. | The global damping factor in expansion scripts. |
| **Viscous Coupling** | The 'grip' of the medium on baryonic matter. | The interaction constant between mass and the fluid. |
